\name{SanitizeWGrib2Inputs}
\alias{SanitizeWGrib2Inputs}
\title{
Make sure regex metacharacters are properly escaped
}
\description{
An internal routine for ensuring that system calls to wgrib2 do not include unescaped regex characters.
}
\usage{
SanitizeWGrib2Inputs(check.strs)
}
%- maybe also 'usage' for other objects documented here.
\arguments{
  \item{check.strs}{
    A vector of strings destined for subset arguments into WGrib2.
}
}
\details{
This is an internal function that helps make sure variable and level names have properly escaped regex characters.
Note that it does not handle backslash.
}
\value{
\item{checked.strs}{A vector of strings with properly escaped regex characters}
}
\author{
Daniel C. Bowman \email{daniel.bowman@unc.edu}
}

\examples{

check.strs <- c("1.2 mb", "3^4 watts")
checked.strs <- SanitizeWGrib2Inputs(check.strs)
print(checked.strs)
}
\keyword{ internal }
